results.name: Sum T(n,k) of the entries in the k-th last blocks of all set partitions of [n]; triangle T(n,k), n>=1, 1<=k<=n, read by rows.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Rows n = 1..100, flattened
example: T(3,2) = 10 because the sum of the entries in the second last blocks of all set partitions of [3] (123, 12|3, 13|2, 1|23, 1|2|3) is 0+3+4+1+2 = 10.
xref: Main diagonal and first lower diagonal give: A000012, A002522.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, May 04 2017
